## Limitations

The findings are based on available data and surveys, which may not capture the full spectrum of reasons for abortion. The data is also subject to reporting biases, as individuals may not disclose all factors influencing their decision. Additionally, the social and legal context of abortion varies significantly across different regions, which can affect the generalizability of the findings.